Put a large #saucepan{} on medium heat and add the @water{750%ml} and
@chicken stock powder{1}. Bring to the boil then reduce the heat to low. Halve,
peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @courgette{1}, quarter
lengthways, then chop widthways into small chunks. Roughly chop the
@flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(stalks and all) then zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}.

Lay two rashers of @streaky bacon rashers{4} on a #board{}, pop a
@cod fillets{2} in the centre and roll up so the bacon encloses the fish. Repeat
for the other fillets. Keep to one side - we will cook the fish later.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Heat a splash of @?oil{} in a wide-bottomed saucepan on medium heat. Add the
shallot. Cook, stirring, until the shallot is soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the
garlic and @tomato puree{1} and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Stir in the
@risotto rice{175%g}, making sure the rice is well coated. Cook for
~{1%minute}.

Stir in a ladle of your stock. When the stock has been absorbed by the rice,
stir in another ladle of stock. Keep the pan on medium heat and continue stirring
in stock, letting it absorb each time. The cooking time should take
~{20-25%minutes} and your risotto is done when your rice is 'al dente' - cooked
through but with a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle. When the risotto
has about 10 mins left, stir in the courgette.

Once you've added the courgette to the rice, heat a splash of @?oil{} in a
#frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, carefully lay in the
fish. Cook on one side until the bacon is browned and crispy, ~{5%minutes}.
Turn the fish over and cook for ~{5%minutes} on the other side, then remove the
pan from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the centre. Keep an eye on your
> risotto as you do this - don't forget to stir!

When the risotto is ready, stir in the @grated hard Italian style cheese{1%tsp},
@unsalted butter{30%g}, a squeeze of lemon juice and half the lemon zest and
parsley. Mix well and season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Pop the
@wild rocket{1%bunch} in a #bowl{} and dress with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and
a squeeze of lemon juice. Spoon the risotto onto your #plates{}. Lay the
fish parcel and rocket alongside and finish with a sprinkling of the remaining
parsley and lemon zest. Enjoy!